  "description": "## Ancient Tomb of Clan Ironfist\n\nA beautifully preserved dwarven tomb with murals depicting Thorgar's heroic deeds and his eventual fall. The tomb features burial chambers, a mural gallery, rune chambers, and the inner sanctum where Thorgar awaits.\n\n### Areas\n- **Entrance Hall** (cells 4,2-10,8): The tomb entrance. Dwarven runes glow faintly on the walls.\n- **Mural Gallery** (cells 19,2-25,8): Murals depicting Thorgar's life, his blessing by Moradin, and his betrayal by his own clan.\n- **Burial Chambers** (cells 4,12-10,18): Where the honored dead of Clan Ironfist rest. Kelda is held here as a living sacrifice.\n- **Rune Chamber** (cells 19,12-25,18): The Runes of Binding — ancient dwarven magic that Thorgar has corrupted. Disabling these weakens him.\n- **Inner Sanctum** (cells 10,22-20,28): Thorgar's final chamber. Contains the Clan Heart, pools of molten metal, and crumbling pillars."
